The paper deals with reinforcement learning for multi-robot sequential assignment planning, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic graphical models and Q-function inference, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper addresses computational scalability, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
